meanwhile in europe nobody speaks the truth that all of the potential millions of migrants and refugees can not be taken into the euro zone former colonial powers like france &amp britain are not without guilt in the creation of the mess that is most of the african continent today
It's important to have honest discussions about migration, but let's also acknowledge the role of historical contexts and global policies that shape these situations. Blaming migrants and refugees overlooks the complexities of their journeys and the shared responsibility we all have in creating a more equitable world.
